@node Fetching geolocation data
@section Fetching geolocation data

@findex calendar-extras-get-geolocation
The function @code{calendar-extras-get-geolocation} performs the HTTP
request to the Geoapify API and parses the JSON response.  It returns
a plist with keys @samp{:lat}, @samp{:lon}, and @samp{:city}.  This function
requires an API key configured via @samp{auth-source-pass}.  It is used by
@code{calendar-extras-set-geolocation} (@ref{Geolocation}) and can also be called
programmatically when you need raw geolocation data without updating
the user options.

@node Enumerating date ranges
@section Enumerating date ranges

@findex calendar-extras-get-dates-in-range
The function @code{calendar-extras-get-dates-in-range} takes two date
strings (START-DATE and END-DATE, in a format understood by
@code{date-to-time}, such as @samp{YYYY-MM-DD}) and returns a list of all dates
between them, inclusive, each formatted as @samp{YYYY-MM-DD}.  This is
useful for generating sequences of dates in scripts or batch
operations.

